Put references in here, in BibLaTeX format.
An easy way to do this is via Zotero, with the Better BibTex extension.
> Create a collection for the specific project, right-click and select Export Collection...
> Choose the Better BibLaTeX format,
  select the 'Keep updated' option,
  and save to output/references.bib (overwriting this file)
Then Zotero will automatically update this file whenever you edit
or add references to the collection.
* Don't manually edit this file, because any changes will be lost next time
  Zotero re-exports from the Collection
* Make sure that any export options set in Zotero are consistent across any machines
  you use this on, otherwise this file will be changed
  - I de-select 'Apply title-casing to titles'
    and 'Apply case-protection to capitalized words by enclosing them in braces',
    and specify "file,abstract" in 'Fields to omit from export'
    (all in the Better BibTeX section of Zotero Settings)
